***************Landing page*******************

I am a Developer in training . Build me a landing page of an online take -away Nigeria meal restaurant with the name MamaPutOnline.

MamaPutOnline sells different types of cooked soups - egusi, ewedu, ora, edikaikong, okazi, ogbono and okro
It also sells jollof rice, fried rice, porridge yam, porridge beans, fried plantain, abacha, nkwobi, fried chicken, kpomo , roosted plantain etc.

UI / UX
Menu Section

Let the landing page have a

- MamaPutOnline logo on the top left hand corner

- Menu bar in dark red with sub titles like Products, Services, Customer Service, Contact Us

- A search window on the very top right hand corner.

Hero Section

Below the menu bar section, let there be a hero section with a Call-To-Action button

The hero section should occupy at least 30% of the vertical length of the page and 100% of the breathe of the page.
A hero section should be vertically partitioned into two

One side of the hero section should display the picture of a steaming, deliciously-cooked Nigerian dish / soup (with the right aspect ratio and with the right pixelization)

The other side of the hero section should have boldly-written words in large print, lettering inviting people to not miss the opportunity to buy from your online store

Main Section
Have a side panel on the left of the main section with items listed there and connecting users to the main section / product cards

Have at least three rows on the landing page...on the right side of the side panel...with each row have 5 product cards

The product cards should identify the product boldly, the quantity and the price in Naira and add a hover effect in the price text and background color changes to a different color from its original color.

Footer

Let the landing page also have a footer that has all the social media l

Build the page using HTML, CSS and / or Tailwind CSS and also use the IDE visual studio code

Make the site fully responsive for mobile users, since many take-away orders will come from smartphones.

Ensure that the Menu and Footer are sticky



***********customer's Service*************
i am a UX designer for Nigerian food delivery brands. 
Design me an ellaborated customer servic epage
Brand: MamaPutOnline 
Target: Busy workers, students, and families in Port Harcourt who want authentic Naija food fast
Tone: Warm, confident, "like your favorite aunty who cooks well", no grammar. Mix English + light Pidgin.
Goal: Make visitor order immediately.

Task: Write a SERVICES section for the landing page.

Requirements:
1. 1 H1 headline: 6-8 words, benefit-driven, mention speed + taste
2. 1 subheadline: 1 sentence explaining the core promise 
3. 3 service cards. Each card needs: 
   - Card title: 2-3 words 
   - Description: 20-25 words, focus on pain point → solution
   - Icon suggestion: Font Awesome icon name
4. 1 CTA button text: 3 words max, action verb
Be specific on the services  we render.
do this with Html and tailwind css, no java script in vs code . it should maintain the same  menu bar and  footer , having the both sticky. 
Thank you Gemini you're the best 


*****************Contact***********************
You are a UX copywriter optimizing forms for WhatsApp-first Nigerian businesses.

Brand: Mama Put Online
Context: Users will order via form, but we reply on WhatsApp in 5 mins. 80% mobile traffic.
Goal: Get name + phone + address + order details with zero friction.

Task: Write all copy for Contact/Order form section.

Requirements:
1. H2 headline: Make user feel chef is waiting for their order
2. Subheadline: Set expectation: reply time + hours
3. Form field labels: Rename boring labels to conversational ones. 5 fields max
4. Placeholder text: For each field, give 1 example in quotes
5. Submit button text: Action + benefit, 4 words max
6. Text under button: Kill last objection about spam/calls

this section should contain our socioal media handle ranging from Facebook, Twitter, Whatsapp, Instagram, Linkedin. and also have a location map and indicate our location in Port Harcourt . 
 Write this Code using html and tailwind css in vs Code

 

